1 planning; and
2 6. Include case management and employment navigation services.
3 (b) To the extent allowable by federal law, utilize federal Supplemental
4 Nutrition Assistance Program matching grant funds as provided in 7 C.F.R.
5 sec. 273.7(d);
6 (c) On or before December 1, 2026, pursue any federal approvals necessary to
7 implement the expansion, including a submission of a state plan
8 amendment to Kentucky's federally approved Supplemental Nutrition
9 Assistance Program education and training plan; and
10 (d) The cabinet shall submit a report to the Legislative Research Commission
11 for referral to the Interim Joint Committee on Health Services and appear
12 before the Interim Joint Committee on Health Services annually to update
13 the members of the committee regarding program participation levels,
14 employment outcomes, healthy workforce outcomes, federal fund draw
15 downs, and program impacts.
